for example, the "NATURAL JOIN", "FULL INNER JOIN", and "LEFT OUTER JOIN" syntaxes are not highlighted as the SELECT, WHERE, etc. syntax is. see attachment for an example of a doc I tried to publish internally.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-1855].
  {panel}

Currently the decorators have no versioning (and no diffing)
So, if you shag the version, the only thing  you can to is go back to the default.

Also worth considering is Themes (I will create a new issue) - ie being able to choose from a set of decorators.

